<%- include('../partials/header') %>

<section class="container page-section content-stack">
  <article class="card-glass content-card reveal">
    <p class="eyebrow">About ORS</p>
    <h1>Designed like a real booking operations platform, not a single-page demo.</h1>
    <p>
      ORS brings flight, train, bus, and hotel reservations into one connected workflow. The platform combines live
      inventory-backed search, booking creation, payment confirmation, passenger tracking, and operational oversight
      through a single full-stack system.
    </p>
  </article>

  <div class="info-grid reveal-group">
    <article class="card-glass info-tile reveal">
      <h3>Unified Search</h3>
      <p>Travelers compare transport and stay options using one interface while the backend keeps each inventory type separate and query-driven.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card-glass info-tile reveal">
      <h3>Reservation Control</h3>
      <p>Seat and room allocation, booking status, payment state, and cancellation handling are preserved across the full reservation lifecycle.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card-glass info-tile reveal">
      <h3>Operational Visibility</h3>
      <p>Admins can manage routes, hotels, pricing, customers, and transaction activity without changing the traveler-facing experience.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
